[SN]TITLE[SN]
European Rugby Challenge Cup: Bath 38-3 Cardiff Blues

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bath ended Cardiff Blues' 100% start in the European Rugby Challenge Cup with a comfortable win at The Rec.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The hosts led at half-time through Ross Batty's try.
Jack Wilson extended their advantage before Cardiff were reduced to 14 men when George Earle was sent off after making contact with an opponent's face.
Aled Brew scored his first try for Bath before Batty intercepted a pass for his second score and Elliott Stooke ran in a late fifth try.
